<title>UK: Crest plans fine system for delaying firms - paper.</title>
<headline>Crest plans fine system for delaying firms - paper.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Crest, the London electronic share settlement system, is drawing up a scale of fines to penalise user companies which cause delays to the system, according to a report in the Daily Telegraph on Monday.</p>
<p>The report also said that Crest plans to call on all users to act as whistle blowers, reporting those companies which have failed to master the system.</p>
<p>Crest staff are trying to target culprit firms which are experiencing problems with the transfer to the new settlement arrangements, said the report. Problems have resulted in investors receiving payments late.</p>
